Section 1:
1 L.D. 1427
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 JUDICIARY
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 936, L.D. 1427, “An Act Extending the
10 Statute of Limitations on Criminal Actions Involving Aggravated Sex Trafficking”
11 Amend the bill by inserting after section 1 the following:
12 'Sec. 2. Report. The Criminal Law Advisory Commission established by the Maine
13 Revised Statutes, Title 5, section 12004-I, subsection 52 shall examine the statutes of
14 limitation in Title 17-A, section 8 pertaining to sexual offenses committed against both
15 adult and minor victims, including by examining whether parity exists between the statutes
16 of limitation established in Title 17-A, section 8, subsection 1, paragraph B and section 8,
17 subsection 2-A, as well as whether the extended limitation periods established in these
18 provisions should apply to any other sexual offense crimes in the State. The commission
19 shall submit a report, including any recommendations, to the Joint Standing Committee on
20 Judiciary no later than December 15, 2025. The committee may report out legislation
21 related to the report to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature.'
22 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
23 number to read consecutively.
24 SUMMARY
2255 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, directs the Criminal
2266 Law Advisory Commission to review and analyze the statutes of limitation within the
2277 Maine Criminal Code pertaining to sexual offenses committed against both adult and minor
2288 victims. The commission must submit a report, including any recommendations, to the
2299 Joint Standing Committee on Judiciary no later than December 15, 2025. The committee
3300 may report out legislation related to the report to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd
3311 Legislature.
3322 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
3333 (See attached)
Page 1 - 132LR0781(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
